topic.title: GCC Configuration and Runtime API

body.p: The GCC block configuration and runtime API are detailed below.

entry.p: Configures Ethernet header fields before GCC trans subsystem enabled.

section.title: g5_api_gcc_header_init_cfg()
section.p: The g5_api_gcc_header_init_cfg() API configures Ethernet header fields before GCC trans subsystem enabled. The API input parameters are described in Table 2 below.

entry.p: Ethertype field of the Ethernet frame.
Software configured overhead in extended header

section.title: g5_api_gcc_filter_init_cfg()
section.p: The g5_api_gcc_filter_init_cfg() API configures GCC trans Ethernet filter before GCC trans subsystem enabled. The API input parameters are described in Table 3 below.

entry.p: VLAN Tag most significant 16 bit value to filter against.
VLAN Tag mask bits to filter most significant 16 bits of VLAN TAG.
Ethertype field of the Ethernet frame.
Ethernet Type that are checked in filter.
Link Mapping Number global filter enable.

section.title: g5_api_gcc_misc_init_cfg()
section.p: The g5_api_gcc_misc_init_cfg() API configures GCC trans MISC configuration before GCC trans subsystem enabled. The API input parameters are described inTable 4 below.

entry.p: HDLC FCS mode for both paths.

section.title: g5_api_gcc_enable_set()
section.p: The g5_api_gcc_enable_set() API enables or disables the GCC trans subsystem. The API input parameters are described in Table 5 below.

entry.p: TRUE: enable GCC trans subsystem. FALSE: disable GCC trans subsystem.

section.title: g5_api_gcc_cfg_get()
section.p: The g5_api_gcc_cfg_get() API gets the GCC Subsystem initial state and GCC header. The API input parameters are described in Table 6 below.
The API output parameter, cfg_ptr, is defined by the g5_gcc_trans_cfg_t structure as described below in Table 7.

entry.p: TRUE: the GCC trans subsystem is enabled. FALSE: the GCC trans subsystem is disabled.
